{"info": {"author": "Alexander Pushkov", "author_email": "alexander@notpushk.in", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# docker-amend\n\n**Install**: `pipx install docker-amend` (plain `pip` works too)\n\n**Usage**: ```docker-amend [OPTIONS] IMAGE COMMAND...```\n\n**Example**:\n\n```\n$ docker build -t my-image .\n...\n$ docker-amend my-image poetry add requests\n$ docker run my-image poetry show\nrequests         2.23.0     Python HTTP for Humans.\n$ grep requests pyproject.toml\nrequests = ^2.23.0\n```\n\n**Options**:\n\n* `-t, --tag NAME[:VERSION]`: Use a different name/tag for the resulting image\n* `-v, --volume SOURCE:TARGET`: Bind mount a volume (assumes --no-pwd-volume)\n* `--no-cwd-volume`: Do not mount cwd as a volume\n* `--install-completion`: Install completion for the current shell.\n* `--show-completion`: Show completion for the current shell, to copy it or customize the installation.\n* `--help`: Show this message and exit.\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://gitlab.com/notpushkin/docker-amend", "keywords": "", "license": "ISC", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "docker-amend", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/docker-amend/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/docker-amend/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://gitlab.com/notpushkin/docker-amend"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/docker-amend/0.1.1/", "requires_dist": ["docker (>=4.2.0,<5.0.0)", "typer (>=0.1.1,<0.2.0)"], "requires_python": ">=3.7,<4.0", "summary": "Amend Docker images by running a command in a separate layer.", "version": "0.1.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>docker-amend</h1>\n<p><strong>Install</strong>: <code>pipx install docker-amend</code> (plain <code>pip</code> works too)</p>\n<p><strong>Usage</strong>: <code>docker-amend [OPTIONS] IMAGE COMMAND...</code></p>\n<p><strong>Example</strong>:</p>\n<pre><code>$ docker build -t my-image .\n...\n$ docker-amend my-image poetry add requests\n$ docker run my-image poetry show\nrequests         2.23.0     Python HTTP for Humans.\n$ grep requests pyproject.toml\nrequests = ^2.23.0\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Options</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>-t, --tag NAME[:VERSION]</code>: Use a different name/tag for the resulting image</li>\n<li><code>-v, --volume SOURCE:TARGET</code>: Bind mount a volume (assumes --no-pwd-volume)</li>\n<li><code>--no-cwd-volume</code>: Do not mount cwd as a volume</li>\n<li><code>--install-completion</code>: Install completion for the current shell.</li>\n<li><code>--show-completion</code>: Show completion for the current shell, to copy it or customize the installation.</li>\n<li><code>--help</code>: Show this message and exit.</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7005528, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "c40e10245d835f0888f29ee8b8259de7", "sha256": "5f1c3a2da36cf433315e5c20747b91741054a25b83936900e1f6bae909ebbf64"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "docker_amend-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "c40e10245d835f0888f29ee8b8259de7", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.7,<4.0", "size": 2365, "upload_time": "2020-04-12T13:20:07", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-12T13:20:07.801169Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/54/1d/79ae520b0587a73a4ef43d7feb72937ceda401639b290ea08768b8c35cad/docker_amend-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "8a39253715fca2f0eeec936af25e69a3", "sha256": "fec9e701b642e9ffa1b31891f8a0f4b33051577e49287b8f2e486d3a95e4d852"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "docker-amend-0.1.0.tar.gz